=begin pod

=head1 NAME

B<Demo> - Demonstrates access to C<$?DISTRIBUTION> and C<%?RESOURCES>
          for installed module distributions

=head1 SYNOPSIS

=begin code :lang<raku>
use Demo;
=end code

=head1 DESCRIPTION

B<Demo> aims to demonstrate use of the special variables,
C<$?DISTRIBUTION> and C<%?RESOURCES>, to access files
included in an installed module distribution.

This module has a binary executable, C<demo>, which, when executed,
shows the results of using the variables to access the following
file (all text files):

=begin code
bin/demo
resources/file1     # <== listed in the C<META6.json> file
resources/file2     # <== listed in the C<META6.json> file
lib/Demo.rakumod    # <== listed in the C<META6.json> file
t/01-basic.rakutest # <== B<NOT> listed in the C<META6.json> file
=end code

